  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently, we use `gasPrice` oracle to offer a suitable gas price for new transactions.\r\nThe underlying mechanism is very simple:\r\n* grab recent blocks(default number is 20)\r\n* sort all recently received transactions by gas-price\r\n* select the suitable recommended gas price by `gpopercentile`\r\n\r\nIt definitely works for full node which has all recent blocks. However it's not cheap for light\r\nclients.  Retrieving 20 block bodies is quite expensive.\r\n\r\nWe need an alternative mechanism for light client `SuggestPriceLight`\r\n\r\nPerhaps the easiest way to achieve it is by using a different lighter default config for light clients.\r\n",
